The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The parameter 'upload_data_size' is declared as a mutable pointer (size_t *upload_data_size) but the function does not modify the pointed-to object (it is only cast to void). According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13, the pointer should point to a const-qualified type when possible — e.g. const size_t *upload_data_size. Therefore, in this translation unit the declaration violates Rule 8.13. (If the external callback API actually requires the function to modify *upload_data_size, the non-const qualification would be justified; however in this code it is unused and could be const.)
